019-10-03}}</ref>\n*\n*\n*\n* \n* \n*\n* Re:\u041f\u0435\u0441\u044c\u043d\u044f\u0440\u044b (author: [[Siarhei Budkin]]) (The festival of advertising and communication \u201cAD.NAK-2015,\u201d 2nd place in the category of socially significant projects)<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://budzma.by/news/pyeramozhcy-ad-nak-2015.html|title=\u041f\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0436\u0446\u044b AD.NAK!-2015|last=|first=|date=2015-07-08|website=|publisher=[[Budzma Belarusians!]]|language=be|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191003060558/https://budzma.by/news/pyeramozhcy-ad-nak-2015.html|archive-date=2019-10-03|access-date=2019-10-03}}</ref>\n* \u0410\u043f\u043e\u0448\u043d\u0456 \u0437\u043e\u043b\u0430\u043a (The festival of advertising and communication \u201cAD.NAK-2015,\u201d 2nd place in the category of socially significant projects)<ref name=\":0\" />\n* The Global Reload project and the competition \u00ab\u0417\u0430\u0441\u044c\u043f\u044f\u0432\u0430\u0439 2.0\u00bb (The Highlights of 2015 by [[Budzma Belarusians!]] in the category of \u201cMain Musical Events of the Year\u201d)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://budzma.by/news/halownyya-padzyei-hoda-pa-vyersii-budzma-byelarusami.html|title=\u0413\u0430\u043b\u043e\u045e\u043d\u044b\u044f \u043f\u0430\u0434\u0437\u0435\u0456 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0430 \u043f\u0430 \u0432\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0456\u0456 \"\u0411\u0443\u0434\u0437\u044c\u043c\u0430 \u0431\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430\u043c\u0456!\"|last=|first=|date=2015-12-24|publisher=[[Budzma Belarusians!]]|language=be|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190925062723/https://budzma.by/news/halownyya-padzyei-hoda-pa-vyersii-budzma-byelarusami.html|archive-date=2019-09-25|access-date=2019-09-25}}</ref>\n* {{ill|Belsat Music Live|be|Belsat Music Live}} (author: Siarhei Budkin) (The Adami Media Prize-2018, Special Mention in the category of \u201cTV Entertainment\u201d)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.adamimediaprize.eu/news/2018/12/5/six-competition-participants-win-adami-media-prize|title=ADAMI Media Prize announces Its six winners!|last=|first=|date=|website=Adami Media Prize for Cultural Diversity in Eastern Europe|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190925061752/https://www.adamimediaprize.eu/news/2018/12/5/six-competition-participants-win-adami-media-prize|archive-date=2019-09-25|access-date=2019-09-25}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [[RSS]]-[http://www.tuzinfm.by/rss.html feed]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8nwc8bbgQxA&list=PLdQABAxpFtAMFr_s4Fe0Y6WHOZlCjATE7 Belsat Music Live playlist (YouTube)]\n\n[[Category:Internet properties established in 2003]]\n[[Category:Media companies of Belarus]]\n[[Category:Media in Minsk]]\n[[Category:Belarusian news websites]]\n[[Category:2003 establishments in Belarus]]\n[[Category:Publications established in 2003]]\n[[Category:Belarusian music websites]]\n", "text_old": "{{expert needed|date=December 2019|reason=It would be helpful for a native speaker to review the sources that are cited to confirm their accuracy. As a non-speaker of Belarusian / Russian, I cannot attest to the sourcing actually supporting the statements listed.}}\n\n{{Infobox website\n| name                 = Tuzin.fm\n| logo                 = Tuzin Gitou.png\n| logo_size            = 250\n| logo_alt             = \n| logo_caption         = <!-- or: | logocaption = -->\n| screenshot           = \n| collapsible          = <!-- set as \"on\", \"y\", etc, otherwise omit/leave blank -->\n| collapsetext         = <!-- collapsible area's heading (default \"Screenshot\"); omit/leave blank if collapsible not set -->\n| background           = <!-- for collapsetext heading; default grey (gainsboro) -->\n| screenshot_size      = \n| screenshot_alt       = \n| caption              = \n| url                  = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->{{URL|tuzinfm.by}}\n| commercial           = <!-- \"Yes\", \"No\" or leave blank -->no\n| type                 = mass media\n| registration         = optional\n| language             = [[Belarusian language|Belarusian]]\n| num_users            = \n| content_license      = <!-- or: | content_licence = -->\n| programming_language = \n| owner                = <!-- or: | owners = -->Anatol' Lazar\n| creators               = <!-- or: creator / authors / creators -->[[Siarhei Budkin]], [[Wiecier Mechaniczny]], Aliaksiej Min\u010donak\n| editor               = <!-- or: | editors = -->\n| launch_date          = <!-- {{Start date and age|df=yes/no|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->{{Start date and age|df=yes|12|10|2003|1}}\n| revenue              = \n| alexa                = <!-- {{IncreaseNegative}} {{Steady}} {{DecreasePositive}} [https://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/example.com example.com Traffic Statistics] --> {{IncreaseNegative}}&nbsp;1,238,976 {{small|{{nowrap|(Global, September 2019)}}}} https://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/tuzinfm.by\n| issn                 = <!-- ISSN, e.g. 1085-6706 (automatically linked to https://www.WorldCat.org) -->\n| eissn                = <!-- eISSN, e.g. 1085-6706 (automatically linked to https://www.WorldCat.org) -->\n| oclc                 = <!-- OCLC number, useful where an ISSN has not been allocated (automatically linked to https://www.WorldCat.org) -->\n| current_status       = active\n| footnotes            = \n}}\n'''Tuzin.fm''' ({{lang-be|\u0422\u0443\u0437\u0456\u043d \u0413\u0456\u0442\u043e\u045e}}; {{trans|A dozen hits}}) is a private non-profit Belarusian web-portal, which was created in 2003 to cover musical creativity in [[Belarus]]. Among its objectives, the site promotes music written in Belarus and motivates to listen to Belarusian songs as large an audience as possible.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://readmemagazine.files.wordpress.com/2011/05/read-me-n2-3d0b3d180.pdf|title=\u041f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442 \u0441\u043a\u043e\u0440\u0435\u0435 \u043c\u0451\u0440\u0442\u0432, \u0447\u0435\u043c \u0436\u0438\u0432|last=\u041a\u0430\u0440\u043f\u0438\u0446\u043a\u0430\u044f|first=\u041a\u0430\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0438\u043d\u0430|year=2011|publisher=Read Me|pages=28\u201330|language=ru|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190915070540/https://readmemagazine.files.wordpress.com/2011/05/read-me-n2-3d0b3d180.pdf|archivedate=2019-09-15|accessdate=2019-09-15|url-status=live|volume=2 (2)}}</ref> It initiates and implements music projects and is the information partner of the most significant events of the Belarusian independent music scene. Independently determining its information policy, the nature and content of the information, advertising, audio, and video materials, in 2009 the mass media had more than 50 thousand monthly visitors who downloaded more than 80 thousand songs.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.experty.by/node/529|title=\"\u0422\u0443\u0437\u0456\u043d \u0413\u0456\u0442\u043e\u045e\" \u0432\u044b\u0434\u0430\u045e \u043b\u0435\u043f\u0448\u044b\u044f \u043f\u0435\u0441\u044c\u043d\u0456 2009|last=|first=|date=2009-12-24|work=|access-date=2019-09-24|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190924085728/http://www.experty.by/content/tuz-n-g-vyda-lepshyya-pesn-2009|archive-date=2019-09-24|publisher=[[Experty.by]]|language=be}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nThe portal began operations on October 12, 2003.<ref>{{Cite journal|year=2005|title=\u0421\u0415\u041c\u042c \u0414\u041d\u0415\u0419 \u0418\u0421\u0422\u041e\u0420\u0418\u0418 \u0411\u0415\u041b\u041e\u0420\u0423\u0421\u0421\u041a\u041e\u0413\u041e \u0420\u041e\u041a-\u041d-\u0420\u041e\u041b\u041b\u0410|url=http://www.nestor.minsk.by/mg/articles/2005/38/1000.html|url-status=live|journal=[[Muzykalnaya Gazeta]]|language=ru|issue=38|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191103090049/http://www.nestor.minsk.by/mg/articles/2005/38/1000.html|archivedate=2019-11-03|accessdate=2019-11-03}}</ref> The site has changed its address several times. Initially, it was available over at music.fromby.net. Later on, the address was changed to tuzin.fm, but after problems with the domain, it was moved to tuzinfm.by. Since May 2017 the portal is available over at tuzin.by too.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.svaboda.org/a/tuzin/27414736.html|title=12 \u0433\u0430\u0434\u043e\u045e \u0431\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043a\u0430\u0433\u0430 \u0440\u043e\u043a\u0443: \u0442\u0443\u0437\u0456\u043d \u043f\u044b\u0442\u0430\u043d\u044c\u043d\u044f\u045e \"\u0422\u0443\u0437\u0456\u043d\u0443 \u0413\u0456\u0442\u043e\u045e\"|last=\u0410\u0410|first=|date=2015-12-09|website=|publisher=[[Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty]]|language=be|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191005091421/https://www.svaboda.org/a/tuzin/27414736.html|archive-date=2019-10-05|access-date=2019-10-05}}</ref> The back catalogue of articles is presented over at [http://mpby.ru mpby.ru].\n\nIn 2004 together with the [[Belarusian Collegium]], it published the book \u00ab{{lang-be|\u0417\u0430\u043b\u0430\u0442\u044b\u044f \u0434\u044b\u0441\u043a\u0456 \u0431\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043a\u0430\u0433\u0430 \u0440\u043e\u043a-\u043d-\u0440\u043e\u043b\u0443}}\u00bb with a description of 20 music albums from the 1970\u20131990 years.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://kamunikat.org/index.php?q=halounaja.html&pubid=3348|title=\u0417\u0430\u043b\u0430\u0442\u044b\u044f \u0434\u044b\u0441\u043a\u0456 \u0431\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043a\u0430\u0433\u0430 \u0440\u043e\u043a-\u043d-\u0440\u043e\u043b\u0430|last=\u0411\u0443\u0434\u043a\u0456\u043d|first=\u0421\u044f\u0440\u0433\u0435\u0439|last2=\u0421\u044c\u0432\u044f\u0440\u0434\u043b\u043e\u045e|first2=\u041f\u0430\u0432\u0430\u043b|date=|website=|publisher=Kamunikat.org|language=be|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190924090923/http://kamunikat.org/index.php?q=halounaja.html&pubid=3348|archive-date=2019-09-24|access-date=2019-09-24|last3=\u0416\u0431\u0430\u043d\u043a\u043e\u045e|first3=\u041c\u0430\u043a\u0441\u0456\u043c}}</ref>\n\nSince 2004, it broadcasts the radio version of its hit parade, entitled \u00ab{{lang-be|\u0420\u0430\u0434\u044b\u0451 \u0422\u0443\u0437\u0456\u043d}}\u00bb, which is anchored by the lead singer of the band {{lang-be|\u041f\u0430\u043b\u0430\u0446}} {{lang-be|\u0410\u043b\u0435\u0433 \u0425\u0430\u043c\u0435\u043d\u043a\u0430}}. From the beginning, airing was on Radio Rocks ([[Minsk]]), since 2005 on Radio Minsk, since 2006 on [[Radio Racyja]] ([[Bia\u0142ystok]]). In 2005\u20132011, it annually releases a compilation of 12 winning songs from the network'''\u2019'''s hit parade called \u00ab{{lang-be|\u041f\u0440\u044d\u043c\u2019\u0435\u0440 \u0422\u0443\u0437\u0456\u043d}}\u00bb (2005,<ref>{{cite book| author1 = {{ill|\u0412\u0456\u0442\u0430\u045e\u0442 \u041c\u0430\u0440\u0442\u044b\u043d\u0435\u043d\u043a\u0430|be-x-old|\u0412\u0456\u0442\u0430\u045e\u0442 \u041c\u0430\u0440\u0442\u044b\u043d\u0435\u043d\u043a\u0430}} | author2 = {{ill|\u0410\u043d\u0430\u0442\u043e\u043b\u044c \u041c\u044f\u043b\u044c\u0433\u0443\u0439|be-x-old|\u0410\u043d\u0430\u0442\u043e\u043b\u044c \u041c\u044f\u043b\u044c\u0433\u0443\u0439}} | chapter = | chapter-url = | format = | url = http://pdf.kamunikat.org/5143-1.pdf | title = 222 \u0430\u043b\u044c\u0431\u043e\u043c\u044b \u0431\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043a\u0430\u0433\u0430 \u0440\u043e\u043a\u0443 \u0456 \u043d\u044f \u0442\u043e\u043b\u044c\u043a\u0456 | orig-year = | agency = [[Vita\u013a Supranovi\u010d|\u0412\u0456\u0442\u0430\u043b\u044c \u0421\u0443\u043f\u0440\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0456\u0447]] | edition =  {{nowrap|2000 \u044d\u043a\u0437}} |location= [[Minsk]] |date = 2006 |publisher= {{ill|\u0411\u041c\u0410group|be|\u0411\u041c\u0410group}} |at=  |volume=  |issue = | pages = 70-73| page =  | series =  | isbn = | ref = }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|year=2005|title=\"\u0422\u0443\u0437i\u043d \u0433i\u0442\u043e\u0443\" \u041f\u0435\u0440\u0432\u044b\u0439 \u0441\u0431\u043e\u0440\u043d\u0438\u043a -- \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0432\u0430\u044f \u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0447\u043a\u0430?|url=http://www.nestor.minsk.by/mg/articles/2005/40/0500.html|journal=[[Muzykalnaya Gazeta]]|language=ru|issue=40|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191103081859/http://www.nestor.minsk.by/mg/articles/2005/40/0500.html|archivedate=2019-11-03|accessdate=2019-11-03|url-status=live}}</ref> 2006, 2007, 2008,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090916021716/http://www.euroradio.fm/by/743/photoreps/27981/|title=\"\u0422\u0443\u0437\u0456\u043d \u0413\u0456\u0442\u043e\u045e\" \u0430\u0434\u0437\u043d\u0430\u0447\u044b\u045e \u044e\u0431\u0456\u043b\u0435\u0439 \u043a\u0430\u043d\u0446\u044d\u0440\u0442\u0430\u043c \u0443 \"\u0413\u0440\u0430\u0444\u0456\u0446\u0456\" (\u0444\u043e\u0442\u0430\u0440\u044d\u043f\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430\u0436)|last=\u041a\u043e\u0442\u043a\u0430|first=\u041c\u0456\u043b\u0430|last2=Tarantino|date=2009-01-28|website=|publisher=[[European Radio for Belarus]]|language=be|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090916021716/http://www.euroradio.fm/by/743/photoreps/27981/|archive-date=2009-09-16|access-date=2019-11-02}}</ref> 2009, 2011). In 2005\u20132007, it took part in the holding of the ceremony of awarding the best musicians of the country \u00ab{{lang-be|\u0420\u043e\u043a-\u043a\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0430\u0446\u044b\u044f}}\u00bb.<ref>{{Cite journal|year=2007|title=\u0421\u0435\u0440\u0433\u0435\u0439 \u0411\u0443\u0434\u043a\u0438\u043d \u041a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u044b \u0437\u0430 2006-\u0439!|accessdate=2019-11-03|url=http://www.nestor.minsk.by/mg/articles/2007/06/0100.html|url-status=live|journal=[[Muzykalnaya Gazeta]]|language=ru|issue=6|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191103074857/http://www.nestor.minsk.by/mg/articles/2007/06/0100.html|archivedate=2019-11-03}}</ref> On March 16, 2006, it held the concert \u201cRock Revolution\u201d in [[Vilnius]] ([[Lithuania]]) with the participation of [[N.R.M.]] In 2006, together with the label VoliaMusic, it published the compilation album \u00ab{{lang-be|\u041f\u0435\u0441\u044c\u043d\u0456 \u0441\u0432\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0434\u044b}}\u00bb. On November 3, 2007, in the [[church of Saints Simon and Helena]] in Minsk, it held a memory concert to collect funds for a monument for poet [[Anatol Sys]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://studfarmat.org/blogs/kancert-pamjaci-anatolja-sysa.html|title=\u041a\u0430\u043d\u0446\u044d\u0440\u0442 \u043f\u0430\u043c\u044f\u0446\u0456 \u0410\u043d\u0430\u0442\u043e\u043b\u044f \u0421\u044b\u0441\u0430|last=|first=|date=2007-10-25|website=|publisher=studfarmat.org|language=be|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100814161314/http://studfarmat.org/blogs/kancert-pamjaci-anatolja-sysa.html|archive-date=2010-09-14|access-date=2019-09-25}}</ref> On August 31, 2008, in Minsk, after a 12-year hiatus, it restored the music festival \u00ab{{lang-be|\u0420\u043e\u043a \u043f\u0430 \u0432\u0430\u043a\u0430\u0446\u044b\u044f\u0445}}\u00bb. On May 23, 2009, at the airport Borovaya ([[Minsk Region|Minsk region]]), it took part in the festival \u201cBela Music,\u201d which was organized by the [[Ministry of Culture of the Republic of Belarus]].\n\nIn 2009 and 2011 together with the public movement [[Budzma Belarusians!]], it released music CDs [[Tuzin. Perazagruzka]] and [[Budzma! Tuzin. Perazagruzka-2]] with translated into [[Belarusian language|Belarusian]] songs by foreign-language performers. In 2011\u20132012 it arranged the acoustic concert series \u00ab{{lang-be|\u0422\u0443\u0437\u0456\u043d. Unplugged}}\u00bb with the participation of [[Rock music in Belarus|Belarusian rock bands]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://budzma.by/news/syamihoddzye-partala-tuzin-hitow-fotarepartazh.html|title=\u0421\u044f\u043c\u0456\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0434\u0437\u0435 \u043f\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430\u043b\u0430 \"\u0422\u0443\u0437\u0456\u043d \u0413\u0456\u0442\u043e\u045e\" (\u0444\u043e\u0442\u0430\u0440\u044d\u043f\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430\u0436)|last=|first=|date=2011-04-27|website=|publisher=[[Budzma Belarusians!]]|language=be|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191209153909/https://budzma.by/news/syamihoddzye-partala-tuzin-hitow-fotarepartazh.html|archivedate=2019-12-09|accessdate=2019-12-09}}</ref> In 2012\u20132013 it held a series of concerts \u00ab{{lang-be|\u0416\u044b\u0432\u044b \u0422\u0443\u0437\u0456\u043d}}\u00bb. In 2012, together with [[Radio Racyja]] ([[Bia\u0142ystok]]), it issued the audiobook \u00ab{{lang-be|\u0414\u0437\u0456\u043d\u044c-\u0434\u0437\u0456\u043b\u0456\u043d\u044c: \u043f\u0430\u0440\u0430 \u0433\u0443\u043b\u044f\u0446\u044c \u0443 \u043a\u0430\u0437\u043a\u0456}}\u00bb by [[Sergey Vitushka]]. In 2012\u20132013 together with the [[Podlasie Opera and Philharmonic]], it prepared a musical voiceover disk of the Belarusian silent film classics \u00ab{{lang-be|\u0422\u0443\u0437\u0456\u043d. \u041d\u0435\u043c\u0430\u045e\u043b\u044f}}\u00bb. In June 2014 together with the [[Viasna Human Rights Centre]], it released the collection of songs \u00ab{{lang-be|\u0410\u043f\u043e\u0448\u043d\u0456 \u0437\u043e\u043b\u0430\u043a}}\u00bb.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://m.tut.by/news/culture/403508.html|title=\u041c\u0443\u0437\u044b\u0447\u043d\u044b \u043f\u0440\u0430\u0435\u043a\u0442 \u0441\u0443\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0446\u044c \u0441\u043c\u044f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u043d\u0430\u0433\u0430 \u043f\u0430\u043a\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044f \"\u0410\u043f\u043e\u0448\u043d\u0456 \u0437\u043e\u043b\u0430\u043a\". \u041f\u0430\u0434\u0432\u043e\u0435\u043d\u0430\u044f \u043f\u0440\u044d\u043c'\u0435\u0440\u0430 TUT|last=|first=|date=2014-06-17|website=|publisher=[[TUT.BY]]|language=be|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190325163525/http://m.tut.by/news/culture/403508.html|archive-date=2019-03-25|access-date=2019-09-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://euroradio.by/ru/aposhni-zolak-ili-vozvrashchenie-sovmestnyh-muzykalnyh-proektov-video|title=\"\u0410\u043f\u043e\u0448\u043d\u0456 \u0437\u043e\u043b\u0430\u043a\" \u0438\u043b\u0438 \u0432\u043e\u0437\u0432\u0440\u0430\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0441\u043e\u0432\u043c\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u043c\u0443\u0437\u044b\u043a\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0435\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0432 (\u0432\u0438\u0434\u0435\u043e)|last=\u041c\u0430\u043b\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439|first=\u0418\u043b\u044c\u044f|date=2013-10-08|website=|publisher=[[European Radio for Belarus]]|language=ru|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20200331072609/https://euroradio.by/ru/aposhni-zolak-ili-vozvrashchenie-sovmestnyh-muzykalnyh-proektov-video|archivedate=2020-03-31|accessdate=2020-03-31|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://euroradio.by/prezentavany-novy-belaruski-supolny-muzychny-praekt-aposhni-zolak-videa|title=\u201c\u0410\u043f\u043e\u0448\u043d\u0456 \u0437\u043e\u043b\u0430\u043a\u201d \u0446\u0456 \u0432\u044f\u0440\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043d\u0435 \u0441\u0443\u043f\u043e\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u043c\u0443\u0437\u044b\u0447\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u043f\u0440\u0430\u0435\u043a\u0442\u0430\u045e (\u0432\u0456\u0434\u044d\u0430)|last=\u041c\u0430\u043b\u0456\u043d\u043e\u045e\u0441\u043a\u0456|first=\u0406\u043b\u043b\u044f|date=2013-10-08|website=|publisher=[[European Radio for Belarus]]|language=be|url-status=live|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20200331073106/https://euroradio.by/prezentavany-novy-belaruski-supolny-muzychny-praekt-aposhni-zolak-videa|archivedate=2020-03-31|accessdate=2020-03-31}}</ref> Also in 2014 together with the Foundation \u00ab{{lang-be|\u0412\u044f\u0440\u0442\u0430\u043d\u044c\u043d\u0435}}\u00bb, it held a contest of young performers \u00ab{{lang-be|\u0417\u0430\u0441\u044c\u043f\u044f\u0432\u0430\u0439.by}}\u00bb,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.svaboda.org/a/29652056.html|title=\"\u0422\u0443\u0437\u0456\u043d\u0443\" \u2014 15. \u042f\u043a \u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430\u0440\u044b\u0446\u044c \u043d\u0430\u0439\u0431\u0443\u0439\u043d\u0435\u0439\u0448\u044b \u043c\u0443\u0437\u044b\u0447\u043d\u044b \u043f\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430\u043b \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0456 \u043d\u0430\u0441\u0443\u043f\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043a \u0443\u0441\u044f\u043c\u0443|last=\u0410\u0417|date=2018-12-12|publisher=[[Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty]]|language=be|trans-title=\u201cTuizin\u201d \u2013 15. How to create the largest music portal in Belarus in spite of everything|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190702052903/https://www.svaboda.org/a/29652056.html|archivedate=2019-07-02|accessdate=2019-07-02|url-status=live}}</ref> another one was opeend in 2017<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://novychas.by/kultura/zaspjavaj-projdze-farmace-4x4|title=\u00ab\u0417\u0430\u0441\u043f\u044f\u0432\u0430\u0439\u00bb \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0439\u0434\u0437\u0435 \u045e \u0444\u0430\u0440\u043c\u0430\u0446\u0435 4x4|last=|first=|date=2017-03-17|website=|publisher=[[Novy Chas]]|url-status=live|language=be|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200209150848/https://novychas.by/kultura/zaspjavaj-projdze-farmace-4x4|archivedate=2020-02-09|accessdate=2020-02-09}}</ref>.\n\nAs a continuation of [[Tuzin. Perazagruzka]] and [[Budzma! Tuzin. Perazagruzka-2]], a new similar project \u201cGlobal Reload\u201d was started in 2014, featuring [[Andrey Makarevich]] and more.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://budzma.by/news/perazahruzka.html|title=\u042f\u043a \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0430\u0433\u0440\u0443\u0437\u0456\u0446\u044c \u0441\u0432\u0435\u0442 \u043c\u0443\u0437\u044b\u043a\u0456 \u0437 \u0443\u043b\u0456\u043a\u0430\u043c \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0456|last=\u0416.|first=\u0413\u0430\u043d\u043d\u0430|date=2018-10-16|publisher=[[Budzma Belarusians!]]|language=be|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191106063429/https://budzma.by/news/perazahruzka.html|archivedate=2019-11-06|accessdate=2019-11-06}}</ref>\n\n== Appraisal ==\nBeing interviewed by [[Muzykalnaya Gazeta]] in 2006, rock-princess [[Rusya]] recognized that the portal, which ''\u201chas'' ''gained momentum,\u201d'' is the godfather of her band [[Indiga (band)|Indiga]].<ref name=\"\u0418\u0442\u043e\u0433\u0438 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0430 2006\">{{Cite journal|first=\u041b\u044e\u0434\u043c\u0438\u043b\u0430|last=\u041f.|url=http://nestor.minsk.by/mg/articles/2007/01/7600.html|title=\u0418\u0422\u041e\u0413\u0418 \u0413\u041e\u0414\u0410: \u041a \u0438\u0442\u043e\u0433\u0430\u043c 2006-\u0433\u043e|language=ru|trans-title=RESULTS OF THE YEAR: About the results of 2006|accessdate=2018-12-03|journal=[[Muzykalnaya Gazeta]]|issue=1|year=2007|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181017203319/http://nestor.minsk.by/mg/articles/2007/01/7600.html|archivedate=2018-10-17|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nDuring the presentation of the compilation album \u201c{{lang-be|\u041f\u0440\u044d\u043c\u2019\u0435\u0440 \u0422\u0443\u0437\u0456\u043d 2007}}\u201d in 2008, musician [[Lavon Volski]] pointed out that Tuzin.fm ''\u201cis the only competent [[hit parade]] in [[Belarus]].\u201d''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://livesound.by/articles/tuzin2007|title=\u00ab\u041f\u0440\u044d\u043c\u2019\u0435\u0440 \u0422\u0443\u0437\u0456\u043d-2007\u00bb \u2014 \u0430\u0434\u0437\u0456\u043d\u044b \u0446\u0456 \u0430\u043f\u043e\u0448\u043d\u0456 \u0437 \u041c\u0430\u0433\u0456\u043a\u0430\u043d?|last=\u041e\u0441\u0438\u043f\u0447\u0438\u043a|first=\u0415\u043a\u0430\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u201cFobia_L\u201d|date=|year=2008|publisher=[[LiveSound.by]]|language=be|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080212141636/http://livesound.by:80/articles/tuzin2007|archivedate=2008-02-12|accessdate=2019-11-22}}</ref>\n\nThe founder of {{ill|Ultra-music.com|be|Ultra-music.com}} Via\u010dasla\u016d Radyjona\u016d gave his assessment of the portal on its seven-year anniversary via [[Budzma Belarusians!]]: ''\u201cThat is a unique and very timely phenomenon. It appeared exactly when Belarusian-language music needed support and the opportunity to bring it to a large audience.\u201d''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://budzma.by/news/syamihoddzye-prayekta-tuzin-hitow-interviyu-z-stvaralnikami.html|title=\u0421\u044f\u043c\u0456\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0434\u0437\u0435 \u043f\u0440\u0430\u0435\u043a\u0442\u0430 \"\u0422\u0443\u0437\u0456\u043d \u0413\u0456\u0442\u043e\u045e\". \u0406\u043d\u0442\u044d\u0440\u0432\u0456\u044e \u0437 \u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0456\u043a\u0430\u043c\u0456|last=|first=|date=2010-10-15|website=|publisher=[[Budzma Belarusians!]]|language=be|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191209145127/https://budzma.by/news/syamihoddzye-prayekta-tuzin-hitow-interviyu-z-stvaralnikami.html|archivedate=2019-12-09|accessdate=2019-12-09}}</ref>\n\nIn a review of all Belarusian music awards for 2013, Paviel Svierdlov, editor of \u201cKYKY.ORG\u201d, criticized the portal because the hit parade did not work for a year, but praised offline activities, ''\u201ctwo excellent projects: \u201c{{lang-be|\u0414\u0437\u0456\u043d\u044c-\u0434\u0437\u0456\u043b\u0456\u043d\u044c: \u041f\u0430\u0440\u0430 \u0433\u0443\u043b\u044f\u0446\u044c \u0443 \u043a\u0430\u0437\u043a\u0456}}\u201d and \u201c{{lang-be|\u0422\u0443\u0437\u0456\u043d.\u041d\u0435\u043c\u0430\u045e\u043b\u044f}}\u201d.\u201d''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kyky.org/music/pliaski-na-kostiakh-rok-karanatsyi-ili-zachiem-bielarusi-shiest-muzykalnykh-priemii|title=\u041f\u043b\u044f\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0441\u0442\u044f\u0445 \u00ab\u0420\u043e\u043a-\u043a\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0430\u0446\u044b\u0456\u00bb, \u0438\u043b\u0438 \u0437\u0430\u0447\u0435\u043c \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 \u0448\u0435\u0441\u0442\u044c \u043c\u0443\u0437\u044b\u043a\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u043c\u0438\u0439|last=\u0421\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0434\u043b\u043e\u0432|first=\u041f\u0430\u0432\u0435\u043b|date=2013-01-31|website=|publisher=KYKY.ORG|language=ru|url-status=live|archiveurl= http://archive.today/EXclY|archivedate=2020-03-21|accessdate=2020-03-21}}</ref>\n\n== Released with the participation of the portal disks ==\n* \u041f\u0440\u044d\u043c\u2019\u0435\u0440 \u0422\u0443\u0437\u0456\u043d (2005\u20132011)\n* \u041f\u0435\u0441\u044c\u043d\u0456 \u0441\u0432\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0434\u044b (2006)\n* [[Tuzin. Perazagruzka]] (2009)\n* [[Budzma! Tuzin. Perazagruzka-2]] (2011)\n* {{lang-be|\u0414\u0437\u0456\u043d\u044c-\u0434\u0437\u0456\u043b\u0456\u043d\u044c: \u041f\u0430\u0440\u0430 \u0433\u0443\u043b\u044f\u0446\u044c \u0443 \u043a\u0430\u0437\u043a\u0456}} (fairytales by Sergey Vitushka)\n* {{lang-be|\u0422\u0443\u0437\u0456\u043d.\u041d\u0435\u043c\u0430\u045e\u043b\u044f}} (disk and art-project, 2012\u20132013)\n* \u0410\u043f\u043e\u0448\u043d\u0456 \u0437\u043e\u043b\u0430\u043a (collaboration project and music compilation, 2013\u20132014)\n* Re:\u041f\u0435\u0441\u044c\u043d\u044f\u0440\u044b (concert and disk, 2014)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kyky.org/cult/iesli-by-mik-dzhaghghier-rodilsia-v-bielarusi-rabotal-by-bukhghaltierom|title=\u0415\u0441\u043b\u0438 \u0431\u044b \u041c\u0438\u043a \u0414\u0436\u0430\u0433\u0433\u0435\u0440 \u0440\u043e\u0434\u0438\u043b\u0441\u044f \u0432 \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438, \u0440\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u0430\u043b \u0431\u044b \u0431\u0443\u0445\u0433\u0430\u043b\u0442\u0435\u0440\u043e\u043c|last=|first=|date=2014-06-27|website=|publisher=KYKY.ORG|language=ru|url-status=live|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20200330163632/https://kyky.org/cult/iesli-by-mik-dzhaghghier-rodilsia-v-bielarusi-rabotal-by-bukhghaltierom|archivedate=2020-03-30|accessdate=2020-03-30|quote=\u0412\u043e\u0442 \u0441\u0435\u0439\u0447\u0430\u0441 \u00ab\u0422\u0443\u0437\u0456\u043d \u0433\u0456\u0442\u043e\u045e\u00bb \u0437\u0430\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0448\u0430\u0435\u0442 \u043f\u0435\u0441\u043d\u044f\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0442\u0440\u0438\u0431\u044c\u044e\u0442-\u043f\u0440\u043e\u0435\u043a\u0442. \u041f\u0440\u0438\u044f\u0442\u043d\u043e \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0439\u0442\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u0441\u0442\u0443\u0434\u0438\u044e \u0438 \u0432\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0435\u0442\u0438\u0442\u044c\u0441\u044f \u0441\u043e \u0432\u0441\u0435\u043c\u0438|author=\u0420\u0443\u0441\u044f|authorlink=Rusya}}</ref>\n\n== Concerts and other projects ==\n\n* \u0417\u0430\u043b\u0430\u0442\u044b\u044f \u0434\u044b\u0441\u043a\u0456 \u0431\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043a\u0430\u0433\u0430 \u0440\u043e\u043a-\u043d-\u0440\u043e\u043b\u0443 (book, 2004)\n* \u0420\u0430\u0434\u044b\u0451\u0422\u0443\u0437\u0456\u043d (radio version of the charts)\n* \u0420\u043e\u043a-\u0440\u044d\u0432\u0430\u043b\u044e\u0446\u044b\u044f (concert in Vilnius, 2006)\n* \u0420\u043e\u043a-\u043a\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0430\u0446\u044b\u044f (2005\u20132007)\n* Concert in memory of Anatoly Sys (2007)\n* \u0420\u043e\u043a \u043f\u0430 \u0432\u0430\u043a\u0430\u0446\u044b\u044f\u0445 (festival, 2008)\n* Bela music (festival, 2008)\n* \u0422\u0443\u0437\u0456\u043d.Unplugged (acoustic concert series, 2011\u20132012)\n* \u0416\u044b\u0432\u044b \u0422\u0443\u0437\u0456\u043d (concert series, 2012\u20132013)\n* \u0417\u0430\u0441\u044c\u043f\u044f\u0432\u0430\u0439.By (contest of young performers, 2014)\n* \u0417\u0430\u0441\u044c\u043f\u044f\u0432\u0430\u0439 2.0 (contest of young performers, 2015)\n* \u0413\u0435\u0440\u043e\u0456 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0443 (musical awards, annual since 2011)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.tut.by/culture/344164.html|title=\u041e\u0442\u0447\u0435\u0433\u043e \u0432 \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438 \u043d\u0435\u0442 \u0441\u0432\u043e\u0435\u0439 \"\u0413\u0440\u044d\u043c\u043c\u0438\"?|last=\u041f\u0440\u043e\u043a\u04