px]]\n<div style=\"margin-left: 60px;\">[[Wikisource]] has original text related to this article:\n<div style=\"margin-left: 10px;\">'''''[[wikisource:Constitution of India/Part III|Fundamental Rights]]'''''<br/> '''''[[wikisource:Constitution of India/Part IV|Directive Principles]]''''' and<br/>'''''[[wikisource:Constitution of India/Part IVA|Fundamental Duties]]'''''</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n{{India topics}}\n{{Featured article}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fundamental Rights, Directive Principles And Fundamental Duties Of India}}\n[[Category:Constitution of India]]\n[[Category:National human rights instruments]]\n", "name_user": "WOSlinker", "label": "safe", "comment": "fix bold", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fundamental_Rights,_Directive_Principles_and_Fundamental_Duties_of_India"}
{"title_page": "Hishiro Station", "text_new": "{{short description|Railway station in Tsukumi, \u014cita Prefecture, Japan}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name                = Hishiro Station\n| native_name         = \u65e5\u4ee3\u99c5\n| native_name_lang    = ja\n| type                = \n| image               = Hisiro20080831.JPG\n| alt                 = \n| caption             = Hishiro Station in 2008\n| address             = \n| borough             = \n| country             = Japan\n| coordinates         ={{coord|33|03|58|N|131|55|07|E|format=dms|source:kolossus-jawiki|display=title,inline}}\n| owned               = \n| operator            = [[File:JR logo (kyushu).svg|20px]] [[JR Kyushu]]\n| line                = {{colorbull|lightskyblue}} [[Nipp\u014d Main Line]]\n| distance            = 184.4 km from {{STN|Kokura}}\n| platforms           = 2 side platform\n| tracks              = 2\n| structure           = At grade\n| parking             = \n| bicycle             = \n| disabled            = No - steep steps to station\n| code                = \n| status              = Unstaffed\n| website             = {{Official website|1=http://www.jrkyushu.co.jp/railway/station/1191803_1601.html}}\n| opened              = {{Start date|1916|10|25|df=y}}\n| former              = \n| closed              = \n| rebuilt             = \n| passengers          = 45 daily\n| pass_year           = FY2015 \n| pass_rank           = \n| map_type            = Japan\n}}\n{{nihongo|'''Hishiro Station'''|\u65e5\u4ee3\u99c5|Hishiro-eki}} is a railway station in [[Tsukumi, \u014cita]], Japan.<ref name=stationmap>{{cite web|url=http://www.jrkyushu.co.jp/english/pdf/jrkyushu_routemap_en.pdf|title=JR Kyushu Route Map|publisher=JR Kyushu|accessdate=23 February 2018}}</ref><ref name=hacchi/>\n\n==Lines==\nThe station is served by the [[Nipp\u014d Main Line]] and is located 184.4&nbsp;km from the starting point of the line at {{STN|Kokura}}.<ref name=kawashima/>\n\n== Layout ==\nThe station, which is unstaffed, consists of two side platforms serving two tracks on an embankment. From the access road, a steep flight of stairs leads up to the station building, a small, modern stonework structure which houses a waiting area and an automatic ticket vending machine. Access to the opposite side platform is by means of a footbridge.<ref name=hacchi>{{cite web|url=http://hacchi-no-he.net/line/nippou/station/0510_hishiro.htm|title=\u65e5\u4ee3|trans-title=Hishiro|accessdate=4 May 2018|website=hacchi-no-he.net}}</ref><ref name=kawashima>{{Cite book|last=Kawashima|first=Ry\u014dz\u014d|script-title=ja: \u56f3\u8aac: \u65e5\u672c\u306e\u9244\u9053 \u56db\u56fd\u30fb\u4e5d\u5dde\u30e9\u30a4\u30f3 \u5168\u7dda\u30fb\u5168\u99c5\u30fb\u5168\u914d\u7dda\u30fb\u7b2c6\u5dfb \u718a\u672c \u5927\u5206 \u30a8\u30ea\u30a2|year=2013 |publisher=Kodansha|isbn=9784062951654|trans-title=Japan Railways Illustrated. Shikoku and Kyushu. All lines, all stations, all track layouts. Volume 6 Kumamoto \u014cita Area|language=Japanese|pages=47, 83}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.misakitty-station.com/sub2-hishiro.htm|title=\u65e5\u4ee3|trans-title=Hishiro|accessdate=4 May 2018}} Blog entry with good photographic coverage of station facilities.</ref>\n\n==Adjacent stations==\n{{j-railservice start}}\n{{j-route|route=Nipp\u014d Main Line|col=lightskyblue|}}\n{{j-rserv|service=Local|next={{STN|Azamui}}|previous={{STN|Tsukumi}}}}\n{{end box}}\n\n==History==\nThe private [[Kyushu Railway]] had, by 1909, through acquisition and its own expansion, established a track from {{STN|Kokura}} to {{STN|Yanagigaura}}. The Kyushu Railway was nationalised on 1 July 1907. [[Japanese Government Railways]] (JGR), designated the track as the H\u014dsh\u016b Main Line on 12 October 1909 and expanded it southwards in phases, with Saiki opening as the new southern terminus on 25 October 1916. On the same day, Hishiro was opened as an intermediate station on the new track. On 15 December 1923, the H\u014dsh\u016b Main Line was renamed the Nipp\u014d Main Line. With the privatization of [[Japanese National Railways]] (JNR), the successor of JGR, on 1 April 1987, the station came under the control of JR Kyushu.<ref>{{Teishajo|I|228-9}}</ref><ref name=teishajo>{{Teishajo|II|755}}</ref>\n\n==Passenger statistics==\nIn fiscal 2015, there were a total of 16,389 boarding passengers, giving a daily average of 45 passengers.<ref name=prefstats>{{cite web|url=http://www.pref.oita.jp/site/toukei/h2811.html|title=\u5e73\u621028\u5e74\u7248\u3000\u5927\u5206\u770c\u7d71\u8a08\u5e74\u9451 11 \u904b\u8f38\u304a\u3088\u3073\u901a\u4fe1|trans-title=Oita Prefecture Statistics Yearbook 2016 Edition Section 11 Transportation and Communications|accessdate=8 April 2018|website=Oita Prefectural Government website}} See table 128 Transport situation by individual railway stations (JR Kyushu JR Freight).</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of railway stations in Japan]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n*[http://www.jrkyushu.co.jp/railway/station/1191803_1601.html Hishiro (JR Kyushu)]{{in lang|ja}}\n\n{{Nipp\u014d Main Line}}\n\n[[Category:Railway stations in \u014cita Prefecture]]\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 1916]]\n\n{{Oita-rail-station-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Railway station in Tsukumi, \u014cita Prefecture, Japan}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name                = Hishiro Station\n| native_name         = \u65e5\u4ee3\u99c5\n| native_name_lang    = ja\n| type                = \n| image               = Hisiro20080831.JPG\n| alt                 = \n| caption             = Hishiro Station in 2008\n| address             = \n| borough             = \n| country             = Japan\n| coordinates         ={{coord|33|03|58|N|131|55|07|E|format=dms|source:kolossus-jawiki|display=title,inline}}\n| owned               = \n| operator            = [[File:JR logo (kyushu).svg|20px]] [[JR Kyushu]]\n| line                = {{colorbull|lightskyblue}} [[Nipp\u014d Main Line]]\n| distance            = 184.4 km from {{STN|Kokura}}\n| platforms           = 2 side platform\n| tracks              = 2\n| structure           = At grade\n| parking             = \n| bicycle             = \n| disabled            = No - steep steps to station\n| code                = \n| status              = Unstaffed\n| website             = {{Official website|1=http://www.jrkyushu.co.jp/railway/station/1191803_1601.html}}\n| opened              = {{Start date|1916|10|25|df=y}}\n| former              = \n| closed              = \n| rebuilt             = \n| passengers          = 45 daily\n| pass_year           = FY2015 \n| pass_rank           = \n| map_type            = Japan\n}}\n{{nihongo|'''Hishiro Station'''|\u65e5\u4ee3\u99c5|Hishiro-eki}} is a railway station in [[Tsukumi, Oita]], Japan.<ref name=stationmap>{{cite web|url=http://www.jrkyushu.co.jp/english/pdf/jrkyushu_routemap_en.pdf|title=JR Kyushu Route Map|publisher=JR Kyushu|accessdate=23 February 2018}}</ref><ref name=hacchi/>\n\n==Lines==\nThe station is served by the [[Nipp\u014d Main Line]] and is located 184.4&nbsp;km from the starting point of the line at {{STN|Kokura}}.<ref name=kawashima/>\n\n== Layout ==\nThe station, which is unstaffed, consists of two side platforms serving two tracks on an embankment. From the access road, a steep flight of stairs leads up to the station building, a small, modern stonework structure which houses a waiting area and an automatic ticket vending machine. Access to the opposite side platform is by means of a footbridge.<ref name=hacchi>{{cite web|url=http://hacchi-no-he.net/line/nippou/station/0510_hishiro.htm|title=\u65e5\u4ee3|trans-title=Hishiro|accessdate=4 May 2018|website=hacchi-no-he.net}}</ref><ref name=kawashima>{{Cite book|last=Kawashima|first=Ry\u014dz\u014d|script-title=ja: \u56f3\u8aac: \u65e5\u672c\u306e\u9244\u9053 \u56db\u56fd\u30fb\u4e5d\u5dde\u30e9\u30a4\u30f3 \u5168\u7dda\u30fb\u5168\u99c5\u30fb\u5168\u914d\u7dda\u30fb\u7b2c6\u5dfb \u718a\u672c \u5927\u5206 \u30a8\u30ea\u30a2|year=2013 |publisher=Kodansha|isbn=9784062951654|trans-title=Japan Railways Illustrated. Shikoku and Kyushu. All lines, all stations, all track layouts. Volume 6 Kumamoto \u014cita Area|language=Japanese|pages=47, 83}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.misakitty-station.com/sub2-hishiro.htm|title=\u65e5\u4ee3|trans-title=Hishiro|accessdate=4 May 2018}} Blog entry with good photographic coverage of station facilities.</ref>\n\n==Adjacent stations==\n{{j-railservice start}}\n{{j-route|route=Nipp\u014d Main Line|col=lightskyblue|}}\n{{j-rserv|service=Local|next={{STN|Azamui}}|previous={{STN|Tsukumi}}}}\n{{end box}}\n\n==History==\nThe private [[Kyushu Railway]] had, by 1909, through acquisition and its own expansion, established a track from {{STN|Kokura}} to {{STN|Yanagigaura}}. The Kyushu Railway was nationalised on 1 July 1907. [[Japanese Government Railways]] (JGR), designated the track as the H\u014dsh\u016b Main Line on 12 October 1909 and expanded it southwards in phases, with Saiki opening as the new southern terminus on 25 October 1916. On the same day, Hishiro was opened as an intermediate station on the new track. On 15 December 1923, the H\u014dsh\u016b Main Line was renamed the Nipp\u014d Main Line. With the privatization of [[Japanese National Railways]] (JNR), the successor of JGR, on 1 April 1987, the station came under the control of JR Kyushu.<ref>{{Teishajo|I|228-9}}</ref><ref name=teishajo>{{Teishajo|II|755}}</ref>\n\n==Passenger statistics==\nIn fiscal 2015, there were a total of 16,389 boarding passengers, giving a daily average of 45 passengers.<ref name=prefstats>{{cite web|url=http://www.pref.oita.jp/site/toukei/h2811.html|title=\u5e73\u621028\u5e74\u7248\u3000\u5927\u5206\u770c\u7d71\u8a08\u5e74\u9451 11 \u904b\u8f38\u304a\u3088\u3073\u901a\u4fe1|trans-title=Oita Prefecture Statistics Yearbook 2016 Edition Section 11 Transportation and Communications|accessdate=8 April 2018|website=Oita Prefectural Government website}} See table 128 Transport situation by individual railway stations (JR Kyushu JR Freight).</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of railway stations in Japan]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n*[http://www.jrkyushu.co.jp/railway/station/1191803_1601.html Hishiro (JR Kyushu)]{{in lang|ja}}\n\n{{Nipp\u014d Main Line}}\n\n[[Category:Railway stations in \u014cita Prefecture]]\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 1916]]\n\n\n{{Oita-rail-station-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ganbaruby", "label": "safe", "comment": "macron", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hishiro_Station"}
